Feature: Companies Management # specs/features/companies.feature:1
  As an analyst or admin
  I want to manage company registry data
  So that monthly cost records can be associated with companies
  Feature: Companies Management  # specs/features/companies.feature:1

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Register a new company           # specs/features/companies.feature:11
    Given the API is running                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given I am on the "New Company" page     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:11
    When I fill in the company form:         # specs/steps/company_steps.py:71
      | field        | value              |
      | company_id   | EMP001             |
      | empresa      | Empresa Alpha      |
      | cnpj         | 98.765.432/0001-10 |
      | razao_social | Alpha Ltda         |
      | cliente      | João Silva         |
      | email_envio  | joao@alpha.com     |
    And I save the company                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:90
    Then the company is created successfully # specs/steps/company_steps.py:220
    And the API returns status 201           # specs/steps/company_steps.py:225
    And I see the company in the list        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:230

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Company requires mandatory fields           # specs/features/companies.feature:27
    Given the API is running                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given I am on the "New Company" page                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:11
    When I leave "empresa" empty                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:76
    And I save the company                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:90
    Then I see a validation error "Empresa is required" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:239
    And the company is not created                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:249

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Company CNPJ must be unique                                 # specs/features/companies.feature:35
    Given the API is running                                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                  # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists with CNPJ "12.345.678/0001-90"               # specs/steps/company_steps.py:49
    When I try to create another company with CNPJ "12.345.678/0001-90" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:81
    And I save the company                                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:90
    Then I see a validation error "CNPJ already exists"                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:239
    And the company is not created                                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:249

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View companies list                                # specs/features/companies.feature:43
    Given the API is running                                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given companies exist in the system                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:19
    When I navigate to "Companies" page                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:213
    Then I see a list of all active companies                  # specs/steps/company_steps.py:254
    And each company shows: company_id, empresa, cnpj, cliente # specs/steps/company_steps.py:258

  @analyst @admin @viewer
  Scenario: View company details                                            # specs/features/companies.feature:50
    Given the API is running                                                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001"                         # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click on the company                                             # specs/steps/company_steps.py:191
    Then I see the full company details                                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:265
    And I see all fields: empresa, cnpj, razao_social, cliente, email_envio # specs/steps/company_steps.py:270

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Update company information              # specs/features/companies.feature:57
    Given the API is running                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001" # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    And I am on the company detail page             # specs/steps/company_steps.py:15
    When I click "Edit Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:108
    And I change the cliente to "Maria Santos"      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:112
    And I click "Update"                            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:116
    Then the company is updated                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:276
    And the cliente shows "Maria Santos"            # specs/steps/company_steps.py:281

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Deactivate a company                          # specs/features/companies.feature:67
    Given the API is running                              # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                    # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP001"       # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click "Deactivate Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:139
    And I confirm company deactivation                    # specs/steps/company_steps.py:143
    Then the company is marked as inactive                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:287
    And it no longer appears in the active companies list # specs/steps/company_steps.py:293
    But its monthly records are preserved                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:304

  @admin
  Scenario: Delete a company                          # specs/features/companies.feature:76
    Given the API is running                          # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists with company_id "EMP003"   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:27
    When I click "Delete Company"                     # specs/steps/company_steps.py:165
    And I confirm company deletion                    # specs/steps/company_steps.py:169
    Then the company is permanently removed           # specs/steps/company_steps.py:310
    And all its monthly records are deleted (CASCADE) # specs/steps/system_steps.py:409

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot create companies         # specs/features/companies.feature:84
    Given the API is running                       # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                             # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given I am logged in as "viewer"               # specs/steps/system_steps.py:68
    When I navigate to the companies page          # specs/steps/company_steps.py:206
    Then I do not see a "New Company" button       # None
    And I cannot access the creation page directly # None

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot edit companies       # specs/features/companies.feature:91
    Given the API is running                   # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                         # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists                     # None
    And I am logged in as "viewer"             # None
    When I view the company details            # None
    Then I do not see an "Edit" button         # None
    And I cannot access the edit page directly # None

  @viewer
  Scenario: Viewer cannot delete companies  # specs/features/companies.feature:99
    Given the API is running                # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                      # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given a company exists                  # None
    And I am logged in as "viewer"          # None
    When I view the company details         # None
    Then I do not see a "Delete" button     # None

Feature: Monthly Cost Records # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:1
  As an analyst
  I want to enter monthly cost data per product
  So that the controller team can track expenses month by month
  Feature: Monthly Cost Records  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:1

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Add monthly record for a product        # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:11
    Given the API is running                        # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                              # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given company "EMP001" exists                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:8
    When I add a monthly record:                    # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:172
      | field          | value      |
      | mes_ano        | 2026-01-01 |
      | produto        | Gympass    |
      | elegiveis      | 100        |
      | vidas_cobradas | 95         |
      | valor_final    | 15000.00   |
    And I save the monthly record                   # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:208
    Then the monthly record is created successfully # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:351
      ASSERT FAILED: Expected 200/201, got 500: {}

    And the monthly API returns status 201          # None

  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Duplicate month detection                                                        # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:25
    Given the API is running                                                                 # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                                                                       # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given company "EMP-DUP" exists                                                           # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:8
    And a monthly record for "EMP-DUP" + "Gympass" + "2026-01-01"                            # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:28
    When I try to add another record for the same company + product + month                  # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:196
    And I save the monthly record                                                            # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:208
    Then I see a monthly validation error "Record already exists for this month and product" # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:369
      ASSERT FAILED: Expected 'Record already exists for this month and product' in response, got: {}


  @analyst @admin
  Scenario: Add multiple products for same month  # specs/features/monthly_records.feature:33
    Given the API is running                      # specs/steps/company_steps.py:7
    And I am logged in                            # specs/steps/system_steps.py:61
    Given company "EMP001" exists                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:8
    When I add a monthly record:                  # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:172
      | field       | value      |
      | mes_ano     | 2026-02-01 |
      | produto     | Gympass    |
      | valor_final | 15000.00   |
    And I save the monthly record                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:208
    And I add another monthly record:             # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:186
      | field       | value      |
      | mes_ano     | 2026-02-01 |
      | produto     | Wiipo      |
      | valor_final | 3000.00    |
    And I save the monthly record                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:208
    Then both records are created                 # specs/steps/monthly_steps.py:445
      ASSERT FAILED: Expected 200/201, got 500

    And I can retrieve both for the same month    # None

